100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On January 18, 1926, British Prime Minister Stanley Baldwin faced growing discontent among coal miners as labor strikes threatened to escalate. In Italy, Benito Mussolini continued to consolidate power, with reports of increased political repression against dissenters. Meanwhile, in the United States, a severe winter storm disrupted transportation and sparked concerns over fuel shortages in several states. The League of Nations remained a focal point for international diplomacy, as tensions in Europe persisted.
